{{Quote|Basilisk blood. It will cooked meat a savory smell. But, if eaten, it produces violent madness in beasts as well as men. A mouse will attack a lion after a taste of basilisk blood. But to a man who his heart, is not passion a form of madness?|[[Oberyn Martell]]|Poisons (Histories &amp; Lore)}}
'''[[Basilisks|Basilisk]]'s blood''' is a [[poison]]. It gives cooked meat a savory smell, but if eaten it causes violent madness, in animals as well as humans.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Poisons (Histories &amp; Lore)]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
